Chop the @cherry tomatoes{1.5} into quarters. Drain and rinse the @organic lentils{1}. Peel and chop the @red onion{1} in half lengthways then slice thinly. Slice the @halloumi{1} into ½cm slices and chop the @pistachios{3}.

Mix the @flour{1} with a pinch of @salt{pinch} and @pepper{pinch} in a #bowl{}. Mix the onion slices in the flour to thoroughly coat them.

Heat @olive oil{1%tbsp} in a #nonstick pan{} on medium-high heat. When the oil is hot, fry off the onion in small batches.

> By not overcrowding the pan you can brown off the onion rather than stew it. When the onion is really crispy, remove to the side (on kitchen towel preferably).

In the (now empty) #pan{}, heat @olive oil{1%tbsp} on medium heat. Add the @ras-el-Hanout{1/2} and cook for ~{1%minute} (with @?sugar{pinch} if you have some). Mix in a third of the tomatoes (½ cup) and season with @salt{1/4%tsp} and a few grinds of @pepper{a few grinds}.

Add half the pack of @basmati rice{1/2} to the pan and stir for ~{1%minute}. Pour in @water{175%ml}(exactly) and turn the heat to its lowest setting. Cover the pan with a #lid{} and leave for ~{10%minutes}. Remove the pan from the heat for ~{10%minutes} (don't remove the lid).

Pre-heat your #grill{} to high. While the grill heats up, brush your halloumi very lightly with @olive oil{}. Lay the slices on a #baking tray{} and grill as close to the heat as possible. Cook until thoroughly browned off on both sides.

Finely chop the @baby spinach{1}. Once the rice is ready, stir in the lentils and half of the onions. Put it back on the #hob{} on medium-low heat for a few mins. Test for seasoning and add more salt and pepper to taste. Lastly, stir the spinach through the rice.

Serve the halloumi on top of your rice, spinach and lentil mixture. Top with the leftover cherry tomatoes, remaining onions and a sprinkle of pistachios.